venance.md lists edgeR as statistical test).\",\n      \"bib_key\": \"Robinson2010\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"authors\": [\n        \"Choi U\",\n        \"Lee CR\"\n      ],\n      \"year\": 2019,\n      \"title\": \"Antimicrobial Agents That Inhibit the Outer Membrane Assembly Machines of Gram-Negative Bacteria\",\n      \"venue\": \"J Microbiol Biotechnol 29(1):1-10\",\n      \"doi\": \"10.4014/jmb.1804.03051\",\n      \"pmid\": \"29996592\",\n      \"pmcid\": null,\n      \"arxiv\": null,\n      \"biorxiv\": null,\n      \"studied\": \"Gram-negative bacteria broadly; Lol (lipoprotein), BAM (OMP), and Lpt (LPS) OM assembly pathways; inhibitor development\",\n      \"finding\": \"Reviews OM component transport machinery (Lol for lipoproteins, BAM for OMPs, Lpt for LPS) and development of inhibitors targeting these systems. OM assembly machines are potential novel antibiotic targets.\",\n      \"scope_alignment\": \"partial\",\n      \"assessment\": \"supports\",\n      \"is_review_article\": true,\n      \"is_preprint\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Background review of OM assembly machines; provides context for Lpt pathway repurposing in Caulobacter (evidence map row 7).\",\n      \"bib_key\": \"Choi2019\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"authors\": [\n        \"Barrows JM\",\n        \"Goley ED\"\n      ],\n      \"year\": 2023,\n      \"title\": \"Synchronized Swarmers and Sticky Stalks: Caulobacter crescentus as a Model for Bacterial Cell Biology\",\n      \"venue\": \"J Bacteriol 205(2):e0038422\",\n      \"doi\": \"10.1128/jb.00384-22\",\n      \"pmid\": \"36715542\",\n      \"pmcid\": \"PMC9945503\",\n      \"arxiv\": null,\n      \"biorxiv\": null,\n      \"studied\": \"C. crescentus as model organism; review of dimorphic life cycle, swarmer/stalked cell biology, appendage biogenesis, cell cycle control, and developmental regulators\",\n      \"finding\": \"C. crescentus exhibits a dimorphic life cycle of motile swarmer and nonmotile stalked cells with tightly controlled biogenesis of appendages and distinct localization of developmental regulators; populations can be synchronized, making it ideal for studies of bacterial differentiation at the single-cell level.\",\n      \"scope_alignment\": \"partial\",\n      \"assessment\": \"supports\",\n      \"is_review_article\": true,\n      \"is_preprint\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Caulobacter model organism review for talk introduction slides; audience orientation to organism context. added by talk\",\n      \"bib_key\": \"Barrows2023\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"authors\": [\n        \"Nierman WC\",\n        \"Feldblyum TV\",\n        \"Laub MT\",\n        \"Paulsen IT\",\n        \"Nelson KE\",\n        \"Eisen JA\",\n        \"Heidelberg JF\",\n        \"Alley MR\",\n        \"Ohta N\",\n        \"Maddock JR\",\n        \"Potocka I\",\n        \"Nelson WC\",\n        \"Newton A\",\n        \"Stephens C\",\n        \"Phadke ND\",\n        \"Ely B\",\n        \"DeBoy RT\",\n        \"Dodson RJ\",\n        \"Durkin AS\",\n        \"Gwinn ML\",\n        \"Haft DH\",\n        \"Kolonay JF\",\n        \"Smit J\",\n        \"Craven MB\",\n        \"Khouri H\",\n        \"Shetty J\",\n        \"Berry K\",\n        \"Utterback T\",\n        \"Tran K\",\n        \"Wolf A\",\n        \"Vamathevan J\",\n        \"Ermolaeva M\",\n        \"White O\",\n        \"Salzberg SL\",\n        \"Venter JC\",\n        \"Shapiro L\",\n        \"Fraser CM\"\n      ],\n      \"year\": 2001,\n      \"title\": \"Complete genome sequence of Caulobacter crescentus\",\n      \"venue\": \"Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A 98(7):4136-4141\",\n      \"doi\": \"10.1073/pnas.061029298\",\n      \"pmid\": \"11259647\",\n      \"pmcid\": \"PMC31192\",\n      \"arxiv\": null,\n      \"biorxiv\": null,\n      \"studied\": \"C. crescentus CB15; 4,016,942 bp single circular chromosome, 3,767 genes; first free-living alphaproteobacterium genome sequenced\",\n      \"finding\": \"Complete genome sequence of C. crescentus CB15: 4,016,9