e 37→42→63 CPM despite borderline single-contrast FDR\n44\t\n45\t_Generated by `notebooks/04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb` cell 7._\n46\t\n47\t### 6. `figures/NB01_leaden_iron_vs_fur.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n48\t\n49\t_PNG, 54.6 KB_\n50\t\n51\t**Best caption candidate:** Leaden internal: Δfur vs iron-limitation response — shows the Fur regulon and iron-limitation response are correlated but not identical, providing Leaden's own validation of the signal\n52\t\n53\t_Generated by `notebooks/01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb` cell 4._\n54\t\n55\t### 7. `figures/NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n56\t\n57\t_PNG, 102.1 KB_\n58\t\n59\t**Best caption candidate:** Leaden Δfur logFC vs our 4584-vs-4580 logFC; concordant_strong in dark blue, buffered set in orange, discordant in red\n60\t\n61\t_Generated by `notebooks/01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb` cell 6._\n62\t\n63\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57c7cd12-ce3b-4c50-865d-721855d63587","uuid":"59686fc5-4e83-47fb-b48e-1fd08461a754","timestamp":"2026-06-08T23:43:13.890Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/aparkin/BERIL-research-observatory/projects/caulobacter_fur_lipida_loss/talks/draft_2/working/curated_figures.md","content":"# Figures Curated for `talk-30`\n\nMode-bounded shortlist of 7 figures (budget 4-10; inventory had 9). The slide-compose prompt makes the final throughline-aware selection from this curated set; figures NOT in the shortlist are still in the full inventory at `figures_inventory.md` if a re-curation is needed.\n\n## Selected figures\n\n### 1. `figures/NB07_synthesis_master.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n\n_PNG, 371.3 KB_\n\n**Best caption candidate:** Master synthesis figure — 4-panel summary of all five mechanism layers\n\n_Generated by `notebooks/07_synthesis.ipynb` cell 2._\n\n### 2. `figures/NB05_pg_remodeling_heatmap.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n\n_PNG, 416.7 KB_\n\n**Best caption candidate:** PG-remodeling enzymes meeting H4 threshold — coordinated up/down pattern across the strain series\n\n_Generated by `notebooks/05_pg_remodeling.ipynb` cell 7._\n\n### 3. `figures/NB04_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n\n_PNG, 204.3 KB_\n\n**Best caption candidate:** Sphingolipid biosynthesis cluster heatmap — flat-to-slightly-decreasing across strain series\n\n_Generated by `notebooks/04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb` cell 5._\n\n### 4. `figures/NB04_lpt_apparatus_heatmap.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n\n_PNG, 114.2 KB_\n\n**Best caption candidate:** Canonical LPS-transport apparatus heatmap — MsbA-like CCNA_00307 visibly UP in 4599 vs others\n\n_Generated by `notebooks/04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb` cell 6._\n\n### 5. `figures/NB04_ctpA_per_strain.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n\n_PNG, 33.9 KB_\n\n**Best caption candidate:** CtpA / CCNA_03113 expression per strain — clear monotonic rise 37→42→63 CPM despite borderline single-contrast FDR\n\n_Generated by `notebooks/04_sphingolipid_lpt_panel.ipynb` cell 7._\n\n### 6. `figures/NB01_leaden_iron_vs_fur.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n\n_PNG, 54.6 KB_\n\n**Best caption candidate:** Leaden internal: Δfur vs iron-limitation response — shows the Fur regulon and iron-limitation response are correlated but not identical, providing Leaden's own validation of the signal\n\n_Generated by `notebooks/01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb` cell 4._\n\n### 7. `figures/NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png` _(source-strength: REPORT-referenced)_\n\n_PNG, 102.1 KB_\n\n**Best caption candidate:** Leaden Δfur logFC vs our 4584-vs-4580 logFC; concordant_strong in dark blue, buffered set in orange, discordant in red\n\n_Generated by `notebooks/01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb` cell 6._\n\n","numLines":63,"startLine":1,"totalLines":63}}}
